<P><FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">&lt;span
style=&quot;color:#00b0f0;&quot; class=&quot;psignal&quot;&gt;
|&lt;/span&gt;</SPAN></FONT>文献调研在线阅读现状：【大阅读环境下高校学生阅读行为调查及图书馆对策
，李铁梅 ，书馆学研究
<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">2011-04-23</SPAN></FONT>】该文指出：纸质阅读与电子阅读成为高校学生最主要的阅读方式。传统的阅读习惯使纸质阅读占有一定地位，而内容丰富、方便快捷的优势使网络、手机等电子阅读方式发起了对纸质阅读的强大冲击。这两种美国图书馆经过大力推行，表明电子阅读在未来不可或缺的地位。然而还存在版权保护，缺乏读者互相交流沟通渠道等问题<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">&lt;span
style=&quot;color:#00b0f0;&quot; class=&quot;psignal&quot;&gt;
|&lt;/span&gt;</SPAN></FONT>需要亟待解决。在线阅读发展迅速，需要丰富交流渠道。【数字阅读<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">,</SPAN></FONT>内容供应才是王道，作者
陈小庚； 钟琳； 陈若然；南方日报
<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">2013-01-13</SPAN></FONT>】该文指出：数字出版的现状：移动平台让更多人开始阅读。
中西比照：数字图书出版要形成产业链。
阅读习惯：阅读变身为“零碎的整合”。数字出版之“太囧”：“阅读设备很好<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">,</SPAN></FONT>但是</P>
<P STYLE="page-break-before: always">读者买不到书”。由此看出，电子阅读虽然丰富了人们的阅读渠道，但读书效果下降了。读者读到的好书少，碎片化，还没有形成产业链。所以，在线阅读需要保证资源的优质。【网络环境下大学生阅读现象分析和思考，吴晶娥情报探索】该文指出：　网络阅读缺少思考。然而<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">,</SPAN></FONT>网上信息虽然丰富多样<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">,</SPAN></FONT>但是无论是好的或有用的信息<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">,</SPAN></FONT>还是一些不良的信息<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">,</SPAN></FONT>读者往往只有被动接受<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">,</SPAN></FONT>如果没有良好的自我管理和控制能力<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">,</SPAN></FONT>就只能花费大量时间在茫茫网海中随波逐流<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">,</SPAN></FONT>失去方向<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">,</SPAN></FONT>无法自拔。长此以往<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">,</SPAN></FONT>将不利于大学生思想的健康成长<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">,</SPAN></FONT>不利于大学生读者人文素养的培养。网络时代阅读环境更加开放、丰富和互动<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">,</SPAN></FONT>拓展了大学生阅读的空间和渠道。图书馆要加强传统纸质书刊的阅读指导<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">,</SPAN></FONT>定期推出新书和好书<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">,</SPAN></FONT>请专家举办阅读讲座<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">,</SPAN></FONT>成立读者好书交流会<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">,</SPAN></FONT>交流阅读体会<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">,</SPAN></FONT>吸引大学生多来图书馆查阅资料<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">,</SPAN></FONT>积极参与图书馆阅读活动<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">,</SPAN></FONT>鼓励大学生多读书<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">,</SPAN></FONT>读好书<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">,</SPAN></FONT>形成良好阅读风气和习惯<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">,</SPAN></FONT>共享阅读乐趣。【网络环境下大学生阅读心理初探张琴办公室业务
<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">2013-01-05
</SPAN></FONT>】大学生阅读需求呈现出多样化，大学生阅读需要的个性化。由于网络所带动的阅读及认知革命还在持续的进行，在正视其不可替代的发展优势的同时，我们还应该根据网络阅读的主体——大学生的阅读心理需求结构的变化而进行适当的调整，帮助他们解决在阅读过程中所遇到的困难，通过对其进行阅读心理调整来提高他们的阅读能力和质量。由此看出，大学生阅读需要引导，需要形成一个良好的阅读环境和习惯。在线阅读需要提供一些良好阅读习惯的引导，才能形成一个良好的社区文化。【肖学斌新环境下图书馆建设与发展——第六届中国社区和乡镇图书馆发展战略研讨</P>
<P STYLE="page-break-before: always">会征文集（下册）【<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">2007-07-01
</SPAN></FONT>中国会议】电子阅读器与手机阅读对比浅析周小琴群文天地<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">2012-08-25
</SPAN></FONT>期刊】该文指出：决定阅读器选择的因素有：性价比影响选择、使用感受差异、便捷性差异、电池续航能力差异、受众使用接受程度差异。从上述几点来看，电子阅读器与手机阅读各有利弊。电子阅读器应抓住自身的专业性，走细分受众市场的道路，将主要功能细化，可以研制商务人士量身定做的商务专业类阅读器；为法律人士开发的涵括各种法律文典著作的阅读器等。例如，以“易博士”电子阅读器为典型进行的行业细分，推出了针对棋谱、司法的行业产品，虽然小众，但针对性强、竞争力小，收获颇佳。对于手机而言，若要走好手机阅读的发展之路，必须提高技术以改善受众的阅读体验。【电子阅读器融入
<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">SNS </SPAN></FONT>方有出路
本报记者 毛启盈 计算机世界<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">2012-04-09
</SPAN></FONT>报纸】该文指出：第一，电子阅读器要彰显“大众化、娱乐化、人性化”的特点。第二，电子阅读器需要
<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">Web2.0
</SPAN></FONT>的互动效果。未来的电子阅读器必将是彩色化、功能多样化，同时增加社交功能等互联网应用。由此看出，在线阅读应该增强用户的阅读体验。摆脱对硬件的依赖，用网络的便利将各种硬件设备体验统一化。【<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">RSS
</SPAN></FONT>在线阅读器设计与实现 王秀慧<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">;
</SPAN></FONT>赵治军电脑编程技巧与维护 <FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">2009-02-18
</SPAN></FONT>期刊】该文指出：基于下架构的在线阅读器的总体设计和实现。实验结果表明该系统的正常运行<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">,</SPAN></FONT>是一个较为完善的、稳定的、灵活的在线阅读系统<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">,
</SPAN></FONT>具有良好的实用价值<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">,</SPAN></FONT>为上网用户信息的获取提供了一个新的途径。【<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">Facilitating
communication about books throughanonline community</SPAN></FONT>】</P>
<P STYLE="page-break-before: always">【 <FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">Malani,
Roshni. Public digital note-taking in lectures. ProQuest
Dissertations andTheses.2009</SPAN></FONT>】【<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">Savage,
John Paul, Jr.. Technography and the sociology of texts: Reading
phenomena inthedigitalhumanities. ProQuest Dissertations and
Theses.2011</SPAN></FONT>】<FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">Reading
books can serve as a means ofgatheringinformation, relaxing and
escaping dailystress. Although reading is often primarily an
individualactivity,many readers also enjoysharing reading experiences
with friends, relatives, colleagues and,through theinternet,even with
strangers. Apart from valuing these individual and collective
bookactivities,books asphysical artifacts are also valued, for
example because of the memoriesassociated withthem. This
paperinvestigates how books can be enhanced with a newproduct, system
or service. In aqualitative interviewstudy, the main reasons for
valuingbooks were found to be related to the self(individual
activities andfeelings), experiences(e.g., enjoyment or release) and
personal values (e.g.,embodiment of idealsorpersonification). As a
result, it was decided for the remainder of this study tofocus
oncommunicationabout books, because in addition to individual
book-related activities andfeelings,users indicated tocommunicate
about books a lot. A book community Web site,called Shelf,
wasdeveloped to investigatewhether book communication could
beincreased by facilitating an onlinecommunity and whether userswould
appreciate theWeb site functionality. Shelf was used in a 14-day
userevaluation, and it wasconcludedthat the Web site increased the
extent to which readers communicatedabout books. We</SPAN></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="page-break-before: always"><FONT FACE="DejaVu Serif, serif"><SPAN LANG="en-US">expect
that such an online book community would be a valuable enhancement of
currentbook customs,inparticular in combination with the current
e-book trend, for various typesof readers who would liketoshare their
experiences.</SPAN></FONT>由此看出：通过书籍的在线社区有助于人们自由地交流思想，观点，使人们相互学习进步
。在线笔记的功能也在国外提出。</P>
